  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1983-04-26", 
    "text": "World War I Veterans' Service Pension Act - Directs the Administrator of Veterans Affairs to pay a monthly service pension of $125 to certain veterans of World War I and the Mexican border period. Increases such pension to $150 if the veteran has a spouse or child. Provides for the payment of a monthly pension of $100 to the surviving spouses of such veterans."
